    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once softened, add the <strong>cooled rice</strong>, your <strong>crab meat </strong>and <strong>soy sauce </strong>and cook for 2-3 min until everything is combined</p><p>Once combined, push the rice to one side of the pan and crack your <strong>egg[s] </strong>into the other side</p><p>Stir the <strong>egg[s]</strong> with a wooden spoon to break the yolk[s] and cook for 1-2 min until it resembles scrambled egg, then mix it all through the rice – this is your <strong>Thai-style crab & egg fried rice</strong></p>",
